
To run this pipeline Snakemake is required.

for easy installation you need (mini)conda.

Miniconda installation:

[wget https://repo.continuum.io/miniconda/Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh]
[bash Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh]

follow the instructions of the installation process, give the location where you want miniconda to be installed and answer YES to add miniconda to your path.


Install the environment using conda:

[conda env create --name  QDNAseq-snakemake --file environment.yaml]

- activate the environment by:

[source activate QDNAseq-snakemake]

Not all packages required by R can be installed by conda, these need to be installed manually from R. first download CGHtest:
# source code at: http://www.few.vu.nl/~mavdwiel/CGHtest.html
wget http://www.few.vu.nl/~mavdwiel/CGHtest/CGHtest_1.1.tar.gz

Than open R and install the Packages using the following code:

R

install.packages("R.cache")
install.packages("gtools")
install.packages("MASS")
install.packages("denstrip")
install.packages("survival")

Installing CGHtest on server:

install.packages("</path/to/>CGHtest_1.1.tar.gz")

        #install.packages('/ccagc/home/matias/tools/CGHtestpar_0.0.tar.gz')

          #library(CGHtest)

install.packages('/net/nfs/PAT/home/matias/tools/CGHtest_1.1.tar.gz')

install.packages("devtools")
library(devtools)

options(unzip = 'internal')
install_github("tgac-vumc/WECCA")
